						<span style="font-size: 15px;" class="button-map-custom"><b>Key Capabilities</b></span>
						<br/><br/>
						<p>
							<img src="images/hpa_1.jpg" alt="CMB LOGO" style="float: left;margin-right:10px">
							An interdisciplinary team provides GIS-based Historical Photographic Analyses and Photogeologic Analyses supporting the Defense Environmental Restoration Program (DERP), Installation Restoration Program (IRP), Formerly Used Defense Sites (FUDS), Base Realignment and Closure (BRAC) and Formerly Utilized Sites Remedial Action Program (FUSRAP) site investigations. The use of Geographic Information Systems (GIS) is a primary component of the work. GIS allows the viewing of multi-layer, "time-sequenced" data in a digital environment. Access to key government, private and scholastic repositories in the National Capital Region equips analysts with a wealth of historical data in order to create a comprehensive understanding of all activities at a project site. Analysts are skilled in using various GIS and remote sensing platforms and applications.
